cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the issue of associating mobile devices to different wireless technologies in a cellular network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a stochastic geometry model to analyze different association policies and optimize performance metrics, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper addresses the problem of harnessing technology and bandwidth diversity in cellular networks, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems engineering. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of different association schemes under different propagation models, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high-quality wireless connectivity. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the issue of associating mobile devices to different wireless technologies can have security implications, such as preventing unauthorized access to the network.
